topic.title: MC Overlay Setting Command

body.p: The MRPC MC Overlay Setting command is used for both Non-Transparent and Switchtec-Specific Multi-cast to configure the overlay for the egress port.

table.title: MC Overlay Setting Command Return Value

entry.p: Invalid Source Partition or Invalid Overlay Size

body.p:
This command has read/write operation modes:
For read operation, the overlay information is copied to an output area for users to access.
For write operation, overlay entry is configured based on the group association, source partition, overlay size, and overlay address.

table.title: MC Overlay Setting Command Input Data

row.entry: Overlay Entry ID, 0 - (Maximum Overlay Number of Current Port-1).

entry.p: Used in conjunction with the Current Partition ID to derive the Physical Port ID. MC overlay entries are allocated based on this value.
Used in conjunction with the Current Partition ID to derive the Physical Port ID.
This register is a bitmap. Each bit (0 to 15 or 0 - 0xFFFF) corresponds to one group.

li.p: 0: Means that all 64 groups are included

entry.p: Only Multicast TLPs from this partition use the overlay configuration of the current entry.

li.p: 48: All partitions use the overlay configuration of the current entry.

entry.p: If this parameter is less than 6, the current entry is invalid. Therefore this parameter can be used to disable the current overlay entry.
Only the highest 26 bits are valid; the lowest 6 bits are ignored.

table.title: MC Overlay Setting Command Output Data (only available for Read operation)

entry.p: Each bit (0 to 15 or 0 - 0xFFFF) corresponds to one group.
0: Means that all 64 groups are included
Other values: Those groups with bit set use the configuration of current entry. A maximum of 16 groups are supported.
Source Partition. Only those Multicast TLPs from this partition use the overlay configuration of the current entry.
0-0x3F: If this parameter is less than 6, it means the current entry is invalid. Therefore, this parameter can be used to disable overlay entry.
Only the highest 26 bits are valid; the lowest 6 bits are ignored.
